<%- content_for(:page_title, "MxMBrook - Marcy\'s Homepage")%>
<%- content_for(:page_description, "MxMBrook.co.uk. This is the personal website of Marcy Brook, a Computer Science student at the University of Sheffield. This site contains a range of tools and projects, as well as a blog.")%>
<article>
  <h1>Welcome!</h1>
  <p>Hi! I'm Marcy, and this is my website.</p>
  <p class="adj">For all information, please visit the <a href="/about">about page</a>.</p>
  <%if @isadmin%>
  <p class="adj">You are logged in as an admin. <a href="/admin">Click here for admin pages</a></p>
  <%end%>
</article>
<main class="indexlayout">
  <div>
    <aside>
      <h2>Quick Access</h2>
      <p><a href="/">Home</a></p>
      <p class="adj"><a href="/tools">Tools</a></p>
      <p class="adj"><a href="/blog">Blog</a></p>
      <p class="adj"><a href="/projects">Projects</a></p>
      <p class="adj"><a href="/about">About</a></p>
      <p class="adj"><a href="/contact">Contact</a></p>
    </aside>
    <aside>
      <h2>What's New?</h2>
      <%if !@seasonal_text.nil?%>
      <h2>Today's Theme</h2>
      <p><%= @seasonal_text%></p>
      <br/>
      <%end%>
      <h3>Dark Mode!</h3>
      <p class="adj" style="font-size:1rem;">This site is now responsive to your system's colour theme! You can emulate this in firefox by adding the property ui.systemUsesDarkTheme to about:config with a value of 1. On chrome, you can emulate it by pressing Ctrl+Shift+I, then F1, and setting Preferences -> Rendering -> "Emulate CSS media feature prefers-color-scheme" to prefers-color-scheme:dark.</p>
      <br/>
      <h3>Latest Tool</h3>
      <p class="adj" style="font-size:1rem;">Ever wondered how many Divs were on a page? Now you can find out!</p>
      <p class="adj"><a href="/tools/divvy">Div Counter</a></p>
    </aside>
  </div>
  <article class="blog">
    <h2>Latest Blog Post:</h2>
    <br/>
    <h2><%=@entry["title"]%></h2>
    <p class="note">Published <%=@entry["date"]%> UTC</p>
    <p class="adj"><%=raw(@entry["content"])%></p>
  </article>
</main>

